parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure leading to Vehicle Stalling and Fire
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall at any speed, leading to a loss of control, and in some cases, catch on fire, posing a significant risk to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls at any speed
popping and cracking sounds from the wiring system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked exhaust manifold can cause exhaust fumes to leak, potentially leading to carbon monoxide poisoning in the passenger compartment, and can also cause engine stalling or fires, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: carbon monoxide leak into passenger compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
The malfunction of the dual tank selector valve can cause the tanks to overpressurize, leading to fuel spills and potentially resulting in a fire.
symptoms: fuel leak at the filler neck
transfer valve fills up the wrong tank
valve leaks when the tank is full.
